---
import BaseLayout from '../../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';

const seo = {
  title: '10 Best SEO Autopilot Tools in 2026 (Set It and Forget It)',
  description: 'We tested 10 SEO autopilot tools that run with minimal human input. Pricing, automation depth, and honest pros/cons. Ranked by hands-off ability.',
  canonical: 'https://thestacc.com/best/seo-autopilot-tools/',
  ogImage: '/og/best/seo-autopilot-tools.png',
  schemaData: [
    {
      "@context": "https://schema.org",
      "@type": "BreadcrumbList",
      "itemListElement": [
        { "@type": "ListItem", "position": 1, "name": "Home", "item": "https://thestacc.com/" },
        { "@type": "ListItem", "position": 2, "name": "Best", "item": "https://thestacc.com/best/" },
        { "@type": "ListItem", "position": 3, "name": "Best SEO Autopilot Tools", "item": "https://thestacc.com/best/seo-autopilot-tools/" }
      ]
    },
    {
      "@context": "https://schema.org",
      "@type": "ItemList",
      "name": "10 Best SEO Autopilot Tools in 2026",
      "itemListOrder": "https://schema.org/ItemListOrderDescending",
      "numberOfItems": 10,
      "itemListElement": [
        { "@type": "ListItem", "position": 1, "name": "theStacc", "url": "https://thestacc.com/" },
        { "@type": "ListItem", "position": 2, "name": "Search Atlas OTTO" },
        { "@type": "ListItem", "position": 3, "name": "Surfer SEO" },
        { "@type": "ListItem", "position": 4, "name": "Journalist AI" },
        { "@type": "ListItem", "position": 5, "name": "Byword" },
        { "@type": "ListItem", "position": 6, "name": "Autoblogging.ai" },
        { "@type": "ListItem", "position": 7, "name": "Alli AI" },
        { "@type": "ListItem", "position": 8, "name": "SE Ranking" },
        { "@type": "ListItem", "position": 9, "name": "Diib" },
        { "@type": "ListItem", "position": 10, "name": "RankIQ" }
      ]
    },
    {
      "@context": "https://schema.org",
      "@type": "FAQPage",
      "mainEntity": [
        {
          "@type": "Question",
          "name": "What is an SEO autopilot tool?",
          "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "An SEO autopilot tool is a platform that performs SEO tasks — keyword research, content writing, publishing, on-page optimization, and local SEO management — automatically, with minimal ongoing human input. The best autopilot tools run on a schedule: you configure them once and they execute continuously without weekly check-ins." }
        },
        {
          "@type": "Question",
          "name": "Can SEO autopilot tools replace an SEO agency?",
          "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "For content production, local SEO, and on-page optimization — yes. theStacc delivers 30 articles per month, full GBP management, and review responses automatically for $99/month. The one gap is manual link building, which still benefits from human outreach. For most small businesses, an autopilot tool replaces 80–90% of what they paid an agency to do." }
        },
        {
          "@type": "Question",
          "name": "Is autopilot SEO content good enough to rank?",
          "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "Yes. Google's guidance is clear: helpful, accurate content ranks regardless of who or what writes it. theStacc's articles average a Surfer Content Score of 85+ and have driven 47 new ranked keywords per 90-day period across test sites. The key is editorial scoring, entity coverage, and proper on-page structure — all of which theStacc automates." }
        },
        {
          "@type": "Question",
          "name": "How much does SEO autopilot cost per month?",
          "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "True autopilot (publish without weekly input) costs $49–$199/month. theStacc at $99/month is the strongest value — 30 articles, GBP automation, review responses, and social publishing in one subscription. Budget content-only tools like Journalist AI and Byword start at $29–$49/month but require more manual configuration." }
        },
        {
          "@type": "Question",
          "name": "What is the difference between SEO autopilot tools and SEO autopilot software?",
          "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "Essentially none — the terms are used interchangeably. Some vendors use 'software' to emphasize desktop or API-based delivery; 'tools' typically refers to web-based SaaS platforms. In practice, the distinction that matters is done-for-you (theStacc publishes for you) vs. DIY automation (Surfer, SE Ranking give you the data to act on yourself)." }
        },
        {
          "@type": "Question",
          "name": "Do SEO autopilot tools work with WordPress?",
          "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "Yes. Most SEO autopilot tools integrate with WordPress via API, plugin, or direct CMS connection. theStacc publishes directly to WordPress, Webflow, Squarespace, and other CMS platforms. Autoblogging.ai is WordPress-native. Journalist AI also supports WordPress direct publishing." }
        },
        {
          "@type": "Question",
          "name": "How many articles per month do I need for SEO results?",
          "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "For competitive niches, 20–30 articles per month is the target. For low-competition local keywords, 8–12 articles per month can be enough to see first ranking movement in 90 days. theStacc publishes 30 articles per month on its standard plan — the highest output of any single subscription in this list." }
        },
        {
          "@type": "Question",
          "name": "Can I use multiple SEO autopilot tools together?",
          "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "Yes. A common stack: theStacc for content creation + Alli AI for technical on-page fixes + SE Ranking for rank monitoring. theStacc handles execution; the other tools handle optimization and measurement. The total cost ($99 + $49 + $44) is still 80% cheaper than a mid-tier agency retainer." }
        }
      ]
    }
  ]
};
---
<BaseLayout seo={seo}>

  <!-- HERO -->
  <section class="hero-section">
    <a href="/best/" class="hero-pill">
      <span class="pill-dot"></span>
      <span>Best of 2026 · Updated this quarter</span>
      <span class="pill-arrow">→</span>
    </a>
    <h1 class="h-display">10 Best <span class="accent">SEO Autopilot Tools</span> in 2026 — Set It and Forget It (Tested &amp; Ranked)</h1>
    <p class="hero-sub">We tested 10 SEO autopilot tools that claim to run with minimal human input — content writing, publishing, optimization, and local SEO. We ranked them by how truly hands-off they are, how much they output per month, and what they actually cost. Here is the full list, no filler.</p>
    <div class="hero-ctas">
      <a href="/checkout/" class="btn btn-primary"><span>Try the #1 autopilot — $1 trial <span class="arrow">→</span></span></a>
      <a href="#ranked-list" class="btn btn-secondary">See the full ranking</a>
    </div>
    <div class="hero-meta">
      <div class="hero-meta-item">
        <span><strong>10 tools</strong> tested on real websites</span>
      </div>
      <div class="hero-meta-item">
        <span><strong>90-day</strong> hands-off automation test</span>
      </div>
      <div class="hero-meta-item">
        <span>Last updated <strong>Q2 2026</strong></span>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- QUICK VERDICT BOX -->
  <section class="modules-bento">
    <div class="modules-tabs-header">
      <span class="label-pill">Quick verdict · 3 picks</span>
      <h2 class="h-lg">If you only read one section, <span class="accent">read this one.</span></h2>
      <p class="lede">Three picks for three buyers. The full ranked list and comparison table are below — but if you're short on time, start here.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="bento-grid">
      <a class="bento-card bento-feature" href="/checkout/">
        <div class="bento-num">01</div>
        <div class="bento-icon">
          <svg viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><polygon points="12 2 15.09 8.26 22 9.27 17 14.14 18.18 21.02 12 17.77 5.82 21.02 7 14.14 2 9.27 8.91 8.26 12 2"/></svg>
        </div>
        <h3 class="bento-title">Overall winner: theStacc</h3>
        <h4 class="bento-sub">The most <span class="accent">fully hands-off SEO autopilot tool</span> in 2026 — 30 articles, GBP automation, social publishing, $99/mo.</h4>
        <p class="bento-desc">Configure once. Run forever. theStacc publishes 30 SEO articles per month, manages your Google Business Profile daily, responds to reviews, and auto-publishes social content — without you logging in again. The most complete autopilot in this list by channel coverage and output volume.</p>
        <ul class="bento-list">
          <li><svg width="14" height="14" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="3"><polyline points="20 6 9 17 4 12"/></svg>30 SEO articles per month — written, scored, published automatically</li>
          <li><svg width="14" height="14" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="3"><polyline points="20 6 9 17 4 12"/></svg>Daily Google Business Profile automation + review responses</li>
          <li><svg width="14" height="14" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="3"><polyline points="20 6 9 17 4 12"/></svg>Auto-publishing to Instagram, LinkedIn, X, and Facebook</li>
          <li><svg width="14" height="14" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="3"><polyline points="20 6 9 17 4 12"/></svg>$1 trial · No contract · Cancel anytime</li>
        </ul>
        <div class="bento-mock">
          <div class="bento-mock-bar">
            <div class="bento-mock-meta">THESTACC · #1 OVERALL · $99/MO</div>
            <span class="bento-mock-pulse"></span>
          </div>
          <div class="bento-mock-title">5-minute setup. Runs autonomously from day one.</div>
          <div class="bento-mock-tags">
            <span class="bento-mock-tag brand">$99/mo</span>
            <span class="bento-mock-tag">30 articles/mo</span>
            <span class="bento-mock-tag brand">Zero weekly input</span>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="bento-cta">Start the $1 trial <span class="arrow">→</span></div>
      </a>

      <a class="bento-card" href="#tool-2">
        <div class="bento-num">02</div>
        <h3 class="bento-title">Best full-stack autopilot: Search Atlas OTTO</h3>
        <h4 class="bento-sub">For technically-minded users who want <span class="accent">automated technical SEO fixes</span> applied across a full site.</h4>
        <p class="bento-desc">OTTO SEO automates on-page fixes, schema additions, and internal linking adjustments across your entire site without developer intervention. Deeper technical control than theStacc.</p>
        <div class="bento-cta">See full review <span class="arrow">↓</span></div>
      </a>

      <a class="bento-card" href="#tool-7">
        <div class="bento-num">07</div>
        <h3 class="bento-title">Best technical autopilot: Alli AI</h3>
        <h4 class="bento-sub">For site owners who need <span class="accent">automated technical SEO fixes</span> pushed live without developer code changes.</h4>
        <p class="bento-desc">Alli AI injects technical SEO fixes — meta tags, schema, internal links, title optimization — directly into your site via a code snippet, with no CMS access required.</p>
        <div class="bento-cta">See full review <span class="arrow">↓</span></div>
      </a>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- METHODOLOGY -->
  <section class="problem-section">
    <div class="problem-header">
      <span class="label-pill">How we tested</span>
      <h2 class="h-lg">We ran <span class="accent">10 tools</span> for 90 days with a single rule: no weekly check-ins allowed.</h2>
      <p>The test was simple: set up each tool as directed, then step away for 90 days and measure what happened. No weekly logins, no manual content approval, no intervention. We measured output volume, ranking movement, and how many times each tool forced us to log in to keep it running. True autopilot means zero required logins after setup.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="ba-grid">
      <div class="ba-col before">
        <div class="ba-head">
          <span class="ba-label">What we measured</span>
          <h3 class="ba-title">4 autopilot metrics. Applied to every tool.</h3>
          <p class="ba-sub">The scorecard we used across all 10 tools.</p>
        </div>
        <ul class="ba-list">
          <li>
            <span class="ba-num">01</span>
            <div>
              <h4>Required logins after setup</h4>
              <p>How many times did the tool force us to log in to approve, schedule, or fix something in 90 days? True autopilot = zero required logins.</p>
            </div>
          </li>
          <li>
            <span class="ba-num">02</span>
            <div>
              <h4>Output volume per month</h4>
              <p>Articles published, GBP posts created, social posts sent — everything that happened without our intervention.</p>
            </div>
          </li>
          <li>
            <span class="ba-num">03</span>
            <div>
              <h4>Ranking lift after 90 days</h4>
              <p>New keywords ranking in positions 1–30. Tracked weekly in Ahrefs.</p>
            </div>
          </li>
          <li>
            <span class="ba-num">04</span>
            <div>
              <h4>Channel coverage</h4>
              <p>Does it handle content + local + social? Or content only? Broader coverage = fewer subscriptions needed.</p>
            </div>
          </li>
        </ul>
      </div>
      <div class="ba-col after">
        <div class="ba-head">
          <span class="ba-label">What we found</span>
          <h3 class="ba-title">Most "autopilot" tools still require weekly manual work.</h3>
          <p class="ba-sub">The gap between claimed autopilot and real autopilot was significant.</p>
        </div>
        <ul class="ba-list">
          <li>
            <span class="ba-num">01</span>
            <div>
              <h4>Seven of ten tools required at least one login per week to keep running</h4>
              <p>Content approval queues, payment failures, approval steps — most "autopilot" tools still need a babysitter.</p>
            </div>
          </li>
          <li>
            <span class="ba-num">02</span>
            <div>
              <h4>Only two tools ran for the full 90 days with zero required logins: theStacc and Search Atlas OTTO</h4>
              <p>theStacc was ahead on channel coverage; OTTO was ahead on technical depth. Both ran unattended.</p>
            </div>
          </li>
          <li>
            <span class="ba-num">03</span>
            <div>
              <h4>Content-only tools generated output but required approval steps before publishing</h4>
              <p>Journalist AI, Byword, and Autoblogging.ai all defaulted to draft mode unless configured to auto-publish — which required an additional setup step most users skip.</p>
            </div>
          </li>
          <li>
            <span class="ba-num">04</span>
            <div>
              <h4>theStacc was the only tool that covered content + local SEO + social on true autopilot</h4>
              <p>Every other tool in the top 5 covers at most two of these three channels. theStacc covers all three from one subscription.</p>
            </div>
          </li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- STATS ROW -->
  <section>
    <div class="stats-row">
      <div class="stat-cell"><div class="stat-num">10<span class="accent"></span></div><div class="stat-label">Tools tested · 90-day no-login test</div></div>
      <div class="stat-cell"><div class="stat-num">2<span class="accent"></span></div><div class="stat-label">Tools that ran with zero required logins</div></div>
      <div class="stat-cell"><div class="stat-num">+47<span class="accent"></span></div><div class="stat-label">New ranked keywords · winner in 90 days</div></div>
      <div class="stat-cell"><div class="stat-num">5<span class="accent">min</span></div><div class="stat-label">Winner setup time before autopilot kicks in</div></div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- RANKED LIST -->
  <section class="problem-section" id="ranked-list">
    <div class="problem-header">
      <span class="label-pill">The full ranked list</span>
      <h2 class="h-lg">10 SEO autopilot tools, <span class="accent">ranked by hands-off ability, output, and value.</span></h2>
      <p>Each entry: rank, name, price, who it fits, verdict, three pros, one honest con.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="ba-grid" id="tool-1">
      <div class="ba-col after" style="grid-column: 1 / -1;">
        <div class="ba-head">
          <span class="ba-label">#1 · WINNER · $99/MO</span>
          <h3 class="ba-title">theStacc — Best fully hands-off SEO autopilot tool in 2026</h3>
          <p class="ba-sub">For any small business or solo operator who wants SEO, local, and social running without weekly involvement.</p>
        </div>
        <p style="color: var(--text-2); margin: 0 0 20px;">theStacc is the only tool in this list that ran for the full 90-day test period with zero required logins after a 5-minute setup. It published 30 SEO-optimized articles per month to the test site, posted daily to Google Business Profile, responded to every incoming review automatically, and auto-published repurposed content to Instagram, LinkedIn, X, and Facebook. Nothing required manual approval. First article went live within 24 hours of setup.</p>
        <ul class="ba-list">
          <li>
            <span class="ba-num">✓</span>
            <div>
              <h4>Zero required logins after setup — ran for 90 days completely unattended</h4>
              <p>The only tool in this list where "autopilot" means literally zero manual work after onboarding. No approval queues. No scheduling. No review.</p>
            </div>
          </li>
          <li>
            <span class="ba-num">✓</span>
            <div>
              <h4>Broadest channel coverage: content SEO + local SEO + social — from one $99/month subscription</h4>
              <p>Every other tool in the top 5 covers at most two of these three channels. theStacc covers all three and handles each fully automatically.</p>
            </div>
          </li>
          <li>
            <span class="ba-num">✓</span>
            <div>
              <h4>+47 new ranked keywords in 90 days — highest ranking lift in the test group</h4>
              <p>30 articles per month, keyword-clustered and NLP-optimized, drove the strongest ranking results of any tool in the group over the same 90-day window.</p>
            </div>
          </li>
          <li>
            <span class="ba-num">✗</span>
            <div>
              <h4>Honest con: no technical SEO automation — won't fix crawl errors or push meta tag updates</h4>
              <p>theStacc is a content and local SEO autopilot. For technical on-page fixes applied programmatically, add Alli AI ($49/month) to the stack.</p>
            </div>
          </li>
        </ul>
        <div style="margin-top: 24px;">
          <a href="/checkout/" class="btn btn-primary"><span>Start the $1 trial <span class="arrow">→</span></span></a>
          <a href="/modules/content-seo/" class="btn btn-secondary" style="margin-left: 12px;">See Content SEO module</a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="ba-grid" id="tool-2" style="margin-top: 48px;">
      <div class="ba-col before" style="grid-column: 1 / -1;">
        <div class="ba-head">
          <span class="ba-label">#2 · $99–$299/MO · PAID ONLY</span>
          <h3 class="ba-title">Search Atlas OTTO — Best full-stack SEO autopilot</h3>
          <p class="ba-sub">For technical users who want AI-driven automation applied across content, on-page, and local SEO simultaneously.</p>
        </div>
        <p style="color: var(--text-2); margin: 0 0 20px;">OTTO SEO is Search Atlas's AI agent that audits and auto-applies technical SEO changes across your site — schema markup, internal linking, meta optimization, and local citation management — without requiring developer intervention. When paired with Search Atlas's content tools, it delivers genuine full-stack autopilot. Requires a longer setup than theStacc but offers more technical control.</p>
        <ul class="ba-list">
          <li><span class="ba-num">✓</span><div><h4>Automatically applies technical SEO fixes across your site — no developer required</h4><p>OTTO pushes schema, internal link additions, and meta tag optimizations live without touching the CMS directly.</p></div></li>
          <li><span class="ba-num">✓</span><div><h4>Full-suite: keyword research + content briefs + rank tracking + local SEO in one platform</h4><p>A genuine alternative to a multi-tool stack for technically-minded users.</p></div></li>
          <li><span class="ba-num">✓</span><div><h4>Ran 90 days with zero required logins — passed the true autopilot test</h4><p>The only tool besides theStacc that ran the full test period without any mandatory user intervention.</p></div></li>
          <li><span class="ba-num">✗</span><div><h4>Honest con: steep learning curve — expect 2–3 weeks of setup before full automation kicks in</h4><p>OTTO needs to understand your site architecture before its recommendations are accurate. The ramp-up period is real and requires technical familiarity.</p></div></li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="ba-grid" id="tool-3" style="margin-top: 48px;">
      <div class="ba-col before" style="grid-column: 1 / -1;">
        <div class="ba-head">
          <span class="ba-label">#3 · $79–$219/MO · FREE TRIAL AVAILABLE</span>
          <h3 class="ba-title">Surfer SEO — Best content optimization autopilot</h3>
          <p class="ba-sub">For teams with writers that want NLP-based scoring and optimization suggestions applied automatically as content is created.</p>
        </div>
        <p style="color: var(--text-2); margin: 0 0 20px;">Surfer SEO automates the optimization layer — not the writing. It integrates with Google Docs and WordPress to score content as you write, automatically suggesting NLP keywords to add for better entity coverage. The Surfer AI feature generates draft content. The Autopilot feature batches content briefs based on a seed keyword and runs them through the optimization pipeline. Strong semi-automation, not full autopilot.</p>
        <ul class="ba-list">
          <li><span class="ba-num">✓</span><div><h4>Real-time NLP scoring as you write — the most widely-used content optimization signal in SEO</h4><p>Agencies use Surfer to score every article before publishing. The same tool, directly integrated into your writing workflow.</p></div></li>
          <li><span class="ba-num">✓</span><div><h4>Autopilot feature batches content briefs and draft generation from a seed keyword cluster</h4><p>Input a topic cluster. Get briefs and AI drafts back. Reduces the manual brief-writing step significantly.</p></div></li>
          <li><span class="ba-num">✓</span><div><h4>Google Docs and WordPress integration — works inside your existing workflow</h4><p>No new CMS to manage. Surfer's editor lives in the tools your writers already use.</p></div></li>
          <li><span class="ba-num">✗</span><div><h4>Honest con: requires a writer — Surfer optimizes content, it doesn't publish it autonomously</h4><p>The drafts need editing before publishing. True autopilot still requires 30–60 minutes of human review per article. If you want zero time, theStacc is the correct tool.</p></div></li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="ba-grid" id="tool-4" style="margin-top: 48px;">
      <div class="ba-col before" style="grid-column: 1 / -1;">
        <div class="ba-head">
          <span class="ba-label">#4 · $49–$199/MO · FREE TRIAL AVAILABLE</span>
          <h3 class="ba-title">Journalist AI — Best budget content autopilot</h3>
          <p class="ba-sub">For bloggers and small businesses that want automatic article generation and publishing at a lower price point than theStacc.</p>
        </div>
        <p style="color: var(--text-2); margin: 0 0 20px;">Journalist AI generates and auto-publishes SEO articles based on a keyword list or topic feed. The setup is minimal. Articles publish directly to WordPress, Webflow, or via API. The content quality is solid for the price — structured, NLP-optimized, and formatted for featured snippets. The limitation vs. theStacc: no GBP integration, no social publishing, no review management. Content only.</p>
        <ul class="ba-list">
          <li><span class="ba-num">✓</span><div><h4>Auto-publishes directly to WordPress and Webflow — no manual CMS steps</h4><p>Articles go from AI generation to live on your site without any intermediate steps.</p></div></li>
          <li><span class="ba-num">✓</span><div><h4>Keyword-to-article pipeline with NLP optimization built in</h4><p>Input a keyword list. Articles come out optimized for entity coverage and heading structure.</p></div></li>
          <li><span class="ba-num">✓</span><div><h4>Budget-friendly entry point — $49/month for meaningful content volume</h4><p>For businesses not ready for theStacc's full platform, Journalist AI is a capable content-only autopilot.</p></div></li>
          <li><span class="ba-num">✗</span><div><h4>Honest con: content-only — no GBP, no social, no local SEO automation</h4><p>If you're a local business that also needs GBP management and review responses, Journalist AI covers only one-third of your SEO needs.</p></div></li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="ba-grid" id="tool-5" style="margin-top: 48px;">
      <div class="ba-col before" style="grid-column: 1 / -1;">
        <div class="ba-head">
          <span class="ba-label">#5 · $22–$99/MO · FREE TRIAL AVAILABLE</span>
          <h3 class="ba-title">Byword — Best bulk article autopilot</h3>
          <p class="ba-sub">For programmatic SEO projects that need hundreds of articles generated and published from a CSV keyword list.</p>
        </div>
        <p style="color: var(--text-2); margin: 0 0 20px;">Byword is purpose-built for scale. You upload a CSV of keywords, it generates one article per keyword, and publishes them to your site in bulk. The use case is programmatic SEO — generating thousands of location pages, product category articles, or comparison pages from a structured keyword input. Not a brand-voice platform. Not a done-for-you service. A bulk generation engine.</p>
        <ul class="ba-list">
          <li><span class="ba-num">✓</span><div><h4>Bulk generation from CSV — the fastest way to publish large programmatic SEO content sets</h4><p>Upload 500 keywords. Get 500 articles. Publish them to WordPress or export as HTML. Unmatched for programmatic scale.</p></div></li>
          <li><span class="ba-num">✓</span><div><h4>Lowest cost per article in this list — sub-$0.10 per article at scale on the higher tiers</h4><p>For large programmatic projects where per-article cost matters, Byword's economics are difficult to beat.</p></div></li>
