          <div class="faq-answer">Yes. Google's guidance is clear: helpful content ranks regardless of who or what writes it. theStacc's articles average a Surfer Content Score of 85+ and drove +47 new ranked keywords per 90-day period across test sites. The key is editorial scoring, entity coverage, and proper on-page structure — all of which theStacc automates.</div>
